HEADWORD: Unsin
<hw>Un*sin"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>sin</ets>.]</ety> <def>To deprive of sinfulness,
as a sin; to make sinless.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Feltham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

